cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use Qubble, please cite the accompanying paper:
  "Globally Charged Vacuum Decay" by G. Barni and J. R. Espinosa,
  arXiv:2606.21653.
title: "Qubble"
abstract: >-
  Qubble is the numerical code accompanying "Globally Charged Vacuum Decay".
  It constructs fixed-charge Euclidean tunnelling saddles for a homogeneous
  medium carrying a conserved global U(1) charge, computes the fixed-Q
  suppression exponent, and uses the Euclidean turning slice as initial data
  for the subsequent Minkowski evolution.
type: software
